<!-- Chosen Palette: Calm Focus (Warm Cream #FDFBF7, Soft Slate #475569, Accessible Teal #0D9488, Alert Amber #D97706) -->
<!-- Application Structure Plan: The app uses a "Dashboard Specification" structure. It is divided into four primary tabs corresponding to the four research areas. This structure reduces cognitive load for the reader (modeling the very principles discussed) by compartmentalizing complex technical requirements into digestible modules.
     1. UX/UI Standards: Interactive cards explaining WCAG/COGA criteria with a 'Simulate Focus Mode' toggle to demonstrate the concept.
     2. AI Interaction: A Split-View showing 'Standard' vs. 'Accessible' LLM outputs to illustrate prompt engineering requirements.
     3. Safety Metrics: A mock analytics dashboard using Chart.js to visualize how behavioral metrics (rage clicks, latency) can be tracked.
     4. Competitive Analysis: A feature comparison matrix using filtered cards.
     The layout prioritizes readability, clear headings, and 'contextual' sidebars that explain the 'Why' behind the 'What'. -->
<!-- Visualization & Content Choices:
     - UX/UI Section: Grid of "Criterion Cards". Interaction: Click to expand technical implementation details. Goal: Inform developers of specific WCAG 2.2 points.
     - AI Section: Text comparison interface. Goal: Demonstrate the difference in reading age/tone.
     - Metrics Section: Chart.js Line Chart (latency tracking) and Bar Chart (error rates). Goal: Visualize abstract behavioral concepts. Interaction: Update data buttons.
     - Competitor Section: Comparison Grid. Goal: Benchmark features.
     - Justification: Charts are used only where quantitative data concepts (metrics) are discussed. Text/Layout is used for qualitative standards. Unicode icons replace SVGs. -->
<!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->

